Message-ID: <cf6eb925-a371-5050-ed5d-01736f0c3b56@roswellpark.org>

On Windows and Mac, we install binary versions of CRAN packages from 
CRAN, rather than building them from source; this is what users would 
do. For unknown reasons, the CRAN packages for R-devel (hence 
Bioc-devel, where your package is not building) are built against 
R-3.4.2, and are not compatible with R-devel. The CRAN packages fail to 
install, hence Bioconductor packages that depend on CRAN packages, 
directly or indirectly, fail to install. There are a large number of these

   http://bioconductor.org/checkResults/3.7/bioc-LATEST/tokay2-index.html

and the only resolution is for CRAN to distribute correct binaries. CRAN 
has been notified of the problem.

Martin


